-- Canadian Tire posts higher profit, appoints new CEO
-- By Sneha Banerjee in Bangalore
-- Thu Aug 07, 2014 08:10AM EDT
-- None



Aug 7 (Reuters) - Retailer Canadian Tire Corp <CTCa.TO> reported a higher quarterly profit and named Michael Medline chief executive, effective Dec. 1

Medline, who will also serve as the president, will take over from Stephen Wetmore, who has agreed to remain on the board in a new, non-executive position of deputy chairman, Canadian Tire said on Thursday. [ID:nCNWQ5h35a]